 the Oasis of Marr camp was really fun today.  Thanks to everyone who turned out and made it a big success!  It was a bit more dangerous than other camps have been -- but as we saw, everyone was quite appreciative of our assistance.<br>
<br>
So here's the question -- where shall our next FA camp be?  Can you guys think of a place most of us can safely go, where people need a lot of help?  Or should we stick to a newbie area next time?<br>
<br>
Post your ideas here -- only two weeks til the next camp! <p><font color=green face="ARIAL, HELVETICA, LUCIDA SANS"><B>Gwion Llewellyn</B></font><BR> Level, um, 36<BR> Bakin' my way to fish roll heaven!<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/unumtini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Numtini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>RA Council Assistant<br><font color=blue>Moderator<b></span><br>  Posts: 217<br> <font color=#006400>(6/25/01 7:01:45 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Thanks! And a question</span><hr size=1> I think we should alternate newbie areas and more advanced areas. Or, do something where we could cover both.<br>
<br>
I'd like to put forth, which I think was originally Ortaak's idea, covering the evil areas. Nektulos, Innothule, and Feerot. There are guard-free places near the newbie zones on all of these. There's always a few newbies in each of these. Nektulos usually has a good number of newbies, the other two are abandoned and very confusing. <br>
<br>
My other choice would be Quenos Hills and Blackburrow, which would cover both a newbie zone and a slightly upper level. We could easily set up an aid station outside of Surefall and another upstairs or at the bridge in blackburrow.<br>
<br>
Kaladim and Butcherblock would be another area which would mix plain newbie with slightly higher level. And the population seems to be fairly high.<br>
<br>
 <p>Numtini Lightheart <br>
Gnomish Warrior of 29 Seasons<br>
Random Acts of Morell-Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/ulegolaasleafmulcher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Legolaas Leafmulcher</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>RA Officer<br><font color=blue>Finrael's nemesis</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#006400>(6/25/01 7:05:00 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Thanks! And a question</span><hr size=1> I know we've done Blackburrow, but have we ever done Qeynos Hills?  Transportation is not *too* bad: into either NK or Toxx.  Tons of lowbies.  And if we set up over near Blackburrow, we could buff people on their way in.<br>
 <p><font size=2 face="verdana,arial"><font color="green"><b>Legolaas Leafmulcher</b></font><br>29th Season Soldier of Tunare<br><br><font color="blue"><b>Finrael Briteside</b></font><br>25th Season Paladin of Tunare<br>Koada'Vie</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/uamerygnmt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AmerygnMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#006400>(6/25/01 7:09:48 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Thanks! And a question</span><hr size=1> Had great fun yesterday - while not a buffer, folks seemed to appreciate my mezzing and slowing of their mobs.  And for some reason, this group of mana-using types hovered around me all the time.. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
For next time, hmm, the Estate of Unrest is a likely candidate - lots of action, lots of folks to help, a serious need for train derailment.  Small area, easy to focus our power in a train situation, folks don't have far to travel when the buffs run out.<br>
<br>
Crushbone and Blackburrow, much the same on a lower level - perhaps the highlevels could set up shop in Unrest while the teens and 20s worked CB?<br>
<br>
My 2 CP...<br>
<br>
Amerygn <p>Amerygn D'Arundel<BR>
Poet & Adventurer of 21 Songs<BR>
Crafter of Fine Armor<BR>
Morell-Thule<BR>
<BR>
<I> While we live, let us live!<I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/brandomacts.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=malinki>Malinki</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>RA Member<b></span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#006400>(6/25/01 7:25:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Thanks! And a question</span><hr size=1> Take your pick, I love Blackburrow, Unrest, Crushbone - I'll be there!  Personally, I think my favorite would be Unrest, but that's only because I'm getting to be a much more comfortable level for the zone. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
However, many also know of my fondness for Blackburrow, and I'd gladly go and hold down the deepest, twistiest, confusingest areas.<br>
<br>
Either of those sounds like a lot of fun to me! <p>Malinki Nuikila<BR>
(Little Big Blade)<BR>
Tree-hugging Warrior of 25 Campaigns</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/uturgut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Turgut</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>RA Member</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#006400>(6/25/01 7:42:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Thanks! And a question</span><hr size=1> I would love to do some train busting in Blackburrow that and I still have score to settle with some of those gnolls.  Qeynos Hills has a lot of traffic and we could supervise small raids to WK.  Now if I was only high enough to take care of the KS'n Guard Nash.<br>
<br>
Turgut Pyrocast<br>
Wizard of the 8th Circle<br>
