Sabinne<br>
Enchantress of the 3rd Season</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/uamerygnmt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AmerygnMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>RA Member</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#006400>(6/25/01 10:01:49 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Thanks! And a question</span><hr size=1> Ally,<br>
<br>
I think that the real issue is that right now, the west half of Antonica is relatively underpopulated.<br>
<br>
When folks like myself, Turgut, Emerest and Wipl were coming up, the area was a lot more crowded.  The Qeynos newbie area, Qeynos Hills and Blackburrow were constantly full, and there was never a problem finding a group, or someone to bind or buff you.<br>
<br>
When I've visited recently, though, it's like a ghost town.  North Qeynos often has 10 or less players, and frequently I'm the only one over 10th level.  I'm usually only in need of a bind when I'm there, but even that can be hard to find.<br>
<br>
In relation to the main topic - since MT ceased to be a &quot;green&quot; server, it looks like that side of the world has quieted down a bit.  I see two consequences for an FA camp - one, not a lot of action, and a lot of that would be alts/twinks (grrr, remembering the 16th Bard yesterday in a full suit of Lambent/SS armor, begging for buffs).  However, the folks genuinely in need, will need help that much more.<br>
<br>
That being said, I'm happy to reprise my train-busting show at the bottom of the ramp in BB, a little mezzing goes a long way there!<br>
<br>
Amerygn <p>Amerygn D'Arundel<BR>
